00:14:01.720 --> 00:14:06.780
So let's say, in general, that we have n bagels and there are k

00:14:07.200 --> 00:14:09.650
kinds of bagels. Well, k kinds

00:14:10.589 --> 00:14:17.329
corresponds to k minus 1 bars. And so the total number of symbols is going to be n, which is the number of

00:14:17.880 --> 00:14:24.169
bagels plus k minus 1, which is the number of dividers. And the number of ways of choosing

00:14:24.720 --> 00:14:29.180
the n bagels when there are k kinds is the number of ways of choosing

00:14:29.790 --> 00:14:35.750
k minus 1 things from a total of n plus k minus 1 slots.

00:14:36.360 --> 00:14:42.500
And symmetrically, that's the same as choosing n things from a situation where there are n

00:14:42.500 --> 00:14:45.289
plus k minus 1 slots. And let me just

00:14:45.660 --> 00:14:51.589
also write that in terms of factorials, if you like. This is n plus k minus 1 factorial

00:14:52.520 --> 00:14:55.300
divided by the product of two factorials,

00:14:55.520 --> 00:14:58.260
n factorial and k minus 1 factorial.

00:14:58.260 --> 00:15:03.020
Brady: "What happens if we have more flavors than we need bagels?

00:15:03.280 --> 00:15:06.220
"Like if you are only buying 5 bagels and there are 10 flavors?"

